name: Demographics
description: Subject-level information such as species, strain, sex, etc.

name: Trial Summary
description: Study-level protocol and treatment information.

name: Subject Elements
description: Chronological order of elements for each subject.

name: Disposition
description: Subject status and study events like death or early termination.

name: Vital Signs
description: Measurements like body temperature, pulse, respiration rate, etc.

name: Body Weight
description: Animal weight over time.

name: Clinical Observations
description: Signs and symptoms observed during the study.

name: Body Weight Gain
description: Derived weight change over time intervals.

name: Laboratory Test Results
description: Clinical pathology results like hematology, chemistry, urinalysis.

name: Macroscopic Findings
description: Gross necropsy findings observed in organs/tissues.

name: Microscopic Findings
description: Histopathological observations in tissues.

name: Reproductive Findings
description: Reproductive system observations (DART-specific).

name: Pup Observations
description: Data about offspring in reproductive or developmental studies.

name: Fetal Pathology
description: Findings from fetal exams during DART studies.

name: Maternal Toxicity
description: Toxicity observations in pregnant females.

name: Pharmacokinetics Concentrations
description: Plasma or serum drug levels.

name: Exposure
description: Dosing information for each subject.

name: Trial Arms
description: Defined treatment groups.

name: Trial Visits
description: Scheduled visits and collection timepoints.

name: Trial Elements
description: Defined parts of the trial like dosing or recovery phases.

name: Findings About
description: Details or clarifications about findings in other domains.

name: Tumor Results
description: Tumor findings in carcinogenicity studies.

name: Tumor Identification
description: Tumor location, type, and relationship to other tumors.

name: Response
description: Response variables such as anti-drug antibodies.

name: Pathology Weights
description: Organ weights at necropsy.

name: Deviations
description: Protocol deviations.

name: Concomitant Medications
description: Medications administered alongside study drugs.

name: ECG Test Results
description: Electrocardiogram measurements.

name: Immunogenicity Specimens
description: Samples collected for immunogenicity testing.

name: Macroscopic Findings
description: Findings visible to the naked eye during necropsy.

name: Microscopic Findings
description: Findings observed via microscope.

name: Food and Water Consumption
description: Daily food and water consumption measurements for animals.

name: Trial Sets
description: Treatment set definitions and parameters for trial arms

name: Comments
description: Study comments, notes, protocol deviations, and additional information.
